### Types of Form Validation

| Type                        | Asan Explanation                                      | Kab Use Karo? |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|---------------|
| **HTML5 Built-in**          | Attributes se automatic validation (no JS needed)     | Simple cases, fast start |
| **JavaScript (Constraint API)** | Custom messages, complex rules, better control       | Advanced validation |
| **Pure JavaScript**         | Manual checking (regex, logic) – full control         | Jab built-in kaafi na ho |

**Best Advice:** Pehle HTML5 attributes use karo, phir JS se improve karo.

### HTML5 Validation Attributes (Sabse Common)

| Attribute          | Kya Karta Hai?                                      | Example |
|--------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|---------|
| `required`         | Field khali nahi chhod sakte                         | `<input required>` |
| `minlength` / `maxlength` | Text ki minimum/maximum length                     | `<input minlength="6" maxlength="12">` |
| `min` / `max`      | Number ya date ke liye range                        | `<input type="number" min="1" max="100">` |
| `step`             | Number mein kitna increment (e.g. 0.5)              | `<input type="number" step="0.5">` |
| `type`             | Email, number, url, date etc. automatic check       | `<input type="email">` |
| `pattern`          | Regular Expression (regex) se custom format         | `<input pattern="[0-9]{5}" title="5 digits">` |

**Note:** `pattern` `<textarea>` pe kaam nahi karta.

### Constraint Validation API (JavaScript)

**Important Properties**

| Property              | Kya Batata Hai? |
|-----------------------|-----------------|
| `element.validity`    | Object jo batata hai kya galat hai (`valueMissing`, `typeMismatch`, `tooShort` etc.) |
| `element.validationMessage` | Browser ka default error message |
| `element.willValidate` | Kya yeh element validate hoga |

**Important Methods**

| Method                    | Kya Karta Hai? |
|---------------------------|----------------|
| `checkValidity()`         | Check karta hai, invalid hone pe `invalid` event fire hota hai |
| `reportValidity()`        | Error message show karta hai |
| `setCustomValidity("msg")`| Custom error message set karta hai (khali string se clear) |

**Simple JS Example:**
```js
const email = document.querySelector("#email");

email.addEventListener("input", () => {
  if (email.validity.typeMismatch) {
    email.setCustomValidity("Please enter a valid email address!");
  } else {
    email.setCustomValidity("");   // clear custom message
  }
});
```

### CSS Styling for Validation States

| Pseudo-class           | Kab Apply Hota Hai? |
|------------------------|---------------------|
| `:valid`               | Jab input sahi hai |
| `:invalid`             | Jab input galat hai |
| `:required`            | Required fields |
| `:user-invalid`        | User ne kuch type kiya aur ab invalid hai (better UX) |
| `:in-range` / `:out-of-range` | Number range ke andar/bahar |

**Example CSS:**
```css
input:invalid {
  border: 2px solid red;
}

input:valid {
  border: 2px solid green;
}

input:required {
  background-color: #fff8e1;
}
